As the country mourns the passing of King Goodwill Zwelithini, Zulu maidens have described the king as a loving father to the nation. eNCA’s Nkosazana Dambuza spoke to some of them and filed this report. Courtesy #DStv403 IMPENDLE- As the country mourns the passing of King Goodwill Zwelithini, Imbokodo – who have for years trekked to the King’s palace during the reed dance are shattered. Zulu maidens have described the king as a loving father to the nation. They say his legacy of protecting the most vulnerable in society will forever live in their hearts. WATCH: King Zwelithini's remains arrive at the royal palace The monarch was interred in a private ceremony, carried out by Amabutho, in the early hours Thursday morning An official memorial service will be held for iSilo Samabandla later in the day.